To calculate the median of an array, we need to first sort the array in ascending order. Then, depending on whether the array length is odd or even, we can determine the median.

Here's the implementation of the function that handles the edge cases and calculates the median:

```javascript
function calculateMedian(arr) {
  // Edge case: empty array
  if (arr.length === 0) {
    return null;
  }

  // Edge case: array with a single element
  if (arr.length === 1) {
    return arr[0];
  }

  // Sort the array in ascending order
  arr.sort((a, b) => a - b);

  // Calculate the median
  const middleIndex = Math.floor(arr.length / 2);
  let median;

  if (arr.length % 2 === 0) {
    // Array length is even, average the two middle elements
    median = (arr[middleIndex - 1] + arr[middleIndex]) / 2;
  } else {
    // Array length is odd, middle element is the median
    median = arr[middleIndex];
  }

  return median;
}
```

