Here is the implementation in JavaScript:

```javascript
function findFirstOccurrence(arr, target) {
  let low = 0;
  let high = arr.length - 1;
  let result = -1;

  while (low <= high) {
    let mid = Math.floor((low + high) / 2);

    if (arr[mid] === target) {
      result = mid;
      high = mid - 1; // Continue searching to the left
    } else if (arr[mid] < target) {
      low = mid + 1;
    } else {
      high = mid - 1;
    }
  }

  return result;
}
```

The time complexity of this algorithm is O(log n) since we are dividing the search space in half with each iteration of the while loop.

