[ 'sentence', 'This', 'is', 'a', 'test' ]
```

In the corrected code, the `replace` method is used to remove punctuation marks by replacing them with an empty string. The regular expression `/[^\w\s]|_/g` matches any character that is not a word character (alphanumeric or underscore) or whitespace.

Then, the sorted words are mapped to only keep the word itself (`[0]` index of the array) and discard the frequency count. This is achieved using `map(([word]) => word)`.

The corrected code will correctly remove punctuation marks and sort the words based on their frequency of occurrence.

